Name: Next
Description: The next instruction that will be executed is the next instruction in the instruction stream

Name: UnconditionalBranch
Description: It's an unconditional branch instruction: #(c:JMP NEAR)#, #(c:JMP FAR)#

Name: IndirectBranch
Description: It's an unconditional indirect branch: #(c:JMP NEAR reg)#, #(c:JMP NEAR [mem])#, #(c:JMP FAR [mem])#

Name: ConditionalBranch
Description: It's a conditional branch instruction: #(c:Jcc SHORT)#, #(c:Jcc NEAR)#, #(c:LOOP)#, #(c:LOOPcc)#, #(c:JRCXZ)#

Name: Return
Description: It's a return instruction: #(c:RET NEAR)#, #(c:RET FAR)#, #(c:IRET)#, #(c:SYSRET)#, #(c:SYSEXIT)#, #(c:RSM)#, #(c:VMLAUNCH)#, #(c:VMRESUME)#, #(c:VMRUN)#, #(c:SKINIT)#

Name: Call
Description: It's a call instruction: #(c:CALL NEAR)#, #(c:CALL FAR)#, #(c:SYSCALL)#, #(c:SYSENTER)#, #(c:VMCALL)#, #(c:VMMCALL)#

Name: IndirectCall
Description: It's an indirect call instruction: #(c:CALL NEAR reg)#, #(c:CALL NEAR [mem])#, #(c:CALL FAR [mem])#
